Rothsay Boys Basketball
September 4 at 5:16 PM ¬∑

Huge shoutout to the following boys on completing the ‚ÄúTiger 5,000 Make Shot Club‚Äù!!

Our Tiger Shot Make Club this offseason (June-August) challenged boys grades 4-12 to see how many shot males they could get on their own! This is time outside of team workouts, team camps, and individual workouts. Great job to these boys as they will be honored between one of our games this coming winter!

Sophomore Wylie Brenden- 5,050 Makes
6th Grader Kellan Simmer- 5,185 Makes
6th Grader Trey Holland- 6,189 Makes
Freshman Matthew Danielson- 6,500 Makes

post_text:
We want to share a Rothsay FFA highlight!

On May 20, Nick Wiezorek, Rothsay FFA‚Äôs very first State FFA Degree Applicant, virtually received his State FFA Degree during the Virtual State FFA Convention. Nearly 300 agricultural education students from across the state were awarded the State FFA Degree during the second day of the 91st Minnesota State FFA Convention.

To be eligible for the State FFA Degree, members must earn and invest at least $2,000 into their Supervised Agricultural Experience (SAE). Candidates must complete a minimum of two years of classroom instruction in an agricultural, food and natural resources education program.

Congratulations, Nick! #WeAreRothsay

post_text:
It‚Äôs times like these that remind us how important community is. So many of us feel helpless but want to HELP (aside from staying home and safe)!

Rothsay staff would like to lead the community in a ‚ÄúGift Card Challenge‚Äù in support of our locals. Mr. Johnson, our Superintendent and HS Principal, is kicking this off by purchasing three $50 gift cards from the Truck Stop, Big J‚Äôs, and The Powerhouse.

Whether you buy them now to use later, or send them to someone out of work, let‚Äôs come together to show our support for the businesses that are limited during this pandemic!

Whatever you can do, whether it‚Äôs $5 or $50, will be appreciated and make an impact! All three places are offering carry out for your safety and convenience.

It takes a village now more than ever, Rothsay! Comment below if you are up for the challenge. And please share!

Proudly, #WeAreRothsay!

Rothsay School Families,

Rothsay School is offering meal delivery (breakfast, lunch, and snack) to our students at their home address during this time. There is NO CHARGE for the meals.

School buses and school personnel will be delivering food to the families who have completed the form or registered over the phone. Delivery times will be communicated as routes are established.

As of now, the vans will leave the school at 9:30 a.m. and deliver the day's lunch and next day's breakfast. You or your student must be available to receive the meal in person.

Food will be delivered to registered home addresses only.

If you are not able to access the below form, you can call the school to register over the phone.

https://drive.google.com/file/d/1oHULliqUksVB0QPAO6bOAn_rm_cOR9o-/view?usp=sharing
